[normal]2.2 The RTPI went through the process of appointing a new CE about 3
[normal] years ago and has therefore has
[normal] recent experience
[normal] to share
[normal]. The Trustees spent some 
[normal]considerable 
[normal]time consid
[normal]ering the type or candidate we
[normal] were looking for and the positioning of t
[normal]he Institute going forward. This work helped to define the search criteria and provided guidance to the 
[normal]Appointment
[normal] Panel.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.3 The Trustees decided it was important for our CE to have profile, both as an individual but also in terms of the Institute. It w
[normal]as important that the new CE was able to work with the highest levels of government (both officials and politicians), business
[normal], across the UK and internationally and also relate to our wide membership base.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.4 The Trustees were well aware of the requirem
[normal]ent to provide a realistic salary which could attract such a candidate. Being based in London also has an impact on the cost of living and the need for an attractive overall package.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.5 
[normal]We went through two recruitment exercises before being able to appoi
[normal]nt an excellent CE, Trudi Elliott CBE. Trudi came to us with experience of national, regional and local government. As the previous Director of the West Midlands Regional Office she had the necessary standing, contacts and profile we were looking for.
[normal]&#xa0;
